README.md
     1‚Üí# Command-line tool
     3‚ÜíThe `mdbook` command-line tool is used to create and build books.
     4‚ÜíAfter you have [installed](../guide/installation.md) `mdbook`, you can run the `mdbook help` command in your terminal to view the available commands.
     5‚Üí
     6‚ÜíThis following sections provide in-depth information on the different commands available.
     7‚Üí
     8‚Üí* [`mdbook init <directory>`](init.md) --- Creates a new book with minimal boilerplate to start with.
     9‚Üí* [`mdbook build`](build.md) --- Renders the book.
    10‚Üí* [`mdbook watch`](watch.md) --- Rebuilds the book any time a source file changes.
    11‚Üí* [`mdbook serve`](serve.md) --- Runs a web server to view the book, and rebuilds on changes.
    12‚Üí* [`mdbook test`](test.md) --- Tests Rust code samples.
    13‚Üí* [`mdbook clean`](clean.md) --- Deletes the rendered output.
    14‚Üí* [`mdbook completions`](completions.md) --- Support for shell auto-completion.

